cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.CV 

The paper presents a method for learning complex structures in large datasets, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method is based on graph theory and can be used to approximate datasets with non-trivial distributions (cs.DM). The paper also mentions applications in biology and astronomy, which are fields that often use machine learning and data analysis techniques (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the ability of the method to deal with noisy data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV).
